nquet that had been set up. She glanced at Hera momentarilly and thought of her father and uncle.<br><br>&quot;Oh Father . . . marrying her off to a mortal to solve this problem? Well, I suppose it is better than to have your own child overthrow you.&quot;<br><br>Athena had heard the reason Zeus and Poseidon backed away from Thetis, and Athena was very displeased with the mere thought. No child of Zeus would ever overpower him. She had already been that legacy and no siblings of hers would stand in the way of her and her Father's power.<br><br>She stood there dressed in her usual golden armor and helmet. Golden chains wrapped lightly against her arms and along the strands of her hair. She looked up with her piercing eyes and grinned seeing Artemis there. <br><br>She walked over towards Hera and Aphrodite and smiled softly.<br>&quot;StepMother.&quot; She nodded a polite bow in her pressence and then turned to Aphrodite. &quot;Sister.&quot;<br><br>She made her appearance to them, and then made her way over to Artemis smiling. &quot;Greetings Sister. This should prove to be an eventful occassion.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 181<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(9/27/01 7:57:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/mogoddessartemis/images/triplemoon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Athena</span><hr size=1> ~she smiled brightly as Athena walked over to her~<br><br>Yes Indeed, this is going to be a very fun day. Weddings usually are..if your in to that kinda thing.<br><br>That, and having the Gods and Goddesses assembled a