ard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Epic: The Trojan War: Wedding of Peleus and Thetis</span><hr size=1> Athena smirked lightly at the mention of the male aspect of Olympus. She thought briefly of Ares an his Amazon woman as well as her other brothers. She could truly care less.<br><br>However, the absense of her Father entrigued her as she missed him so.<br><br>She rose a goblet to her lips taking a sip of the nectar and glanced about as the wedding seemed to be starting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/19/01 11:11:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic: The Trojan War: Wedding of Peleus and Thetis</span><hr size=1> Hera laughed softly, &quot;Well, it is probably best that the Gods do not show up.  Or they would all want to wisk the beautiful Thetis away and have her for their very own.&quot;  <br><br>The Queen of the Gods had always been watchful of any who caught her husband's eyes.  But, unfortantly there were many.  And at times, so many that it was hard to keep up with them.  Hopefully, Thetis being married would keep him from at least that one conquest. <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/19/01 1:51:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic: The Trojan War: Wedding of Peleus and Thetis</span><hr size=1> ::Hades sat in his throne in the Underworld.  His facial expression somber as usual.  He then stood up and walked to the tower of his palace.  With that a Shade walked up behind him::<br><br>~Exhalted one...News from the world above.  There is a wedding currently going on.  Thetis is marrying Peleus.  Will you be attending sir?  Tyresius and some of the other soothsayers are saying that...~<br><br>::Hades raised his right hand to silence the Shade, he then turned to look at the Shade with narrowed eyes.  The Shade shuttered in fear as it bowed before Hades who was now facing him.  Hades finally spoke::<br>&quot;I know what the Soothsayers have said.  Do not concern yourself with such matters.&quot;<br><br>::Hades walked back into his throne room and sat down regally in his throne.  No Lord Hades was not going to be attending this event:: <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A> at: 10/19/01 1:52:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uzeuskingofthegods.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zeus King of the Gods</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/19/01 9:23:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The King of the Gods Arrives</span><hr size=1> Zeus was busy frolicking with the nymphs when Hermes alerted him to the fact that there was to be a wedding of such importance that he mustn't miss it.  Hermes also added that Hera was pacing and looking a bit grim at his presence not being there.<br><br>He grinned at the nymphs, &quot;Ahh, my ladies, I must bid you adieu until the morrow.&quot;  With a loud clap of thunder and a flash of lightning, he disappeared from their midst.<br><br>En route to the wedding, he donned himself in the typical white toga, with gold items securing it in place.  The glow of this deity was enough to outshine Apollo should he desire to do so.  As he appeared at the wedding, his smile broadened across his face.  Even as the king of the gods, he was proud of his Olympian family and the offshoots of that family.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hypnos>Hypnos </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 194<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/20/01 10:11:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=C:\WINDOWS\Desktop\Stuff\hypnos.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ***Hypnos Appears***</span><hr size=1> ***In a flash of blue light, black smoke, and some swirling raindrops, Hypnos appears. He smiles as he looks around at the joyious occassion, especially with most of the gods and goddesses there. He wears a toga made of a sky blue silk, and a cape of a lavender colored silk as well. He also wears silver sandles, his horn of sleep slung arround his arm with a blue and purple twisted cord holding it, and his silver mask with a blue dimond encrested on the front. He then walked over to the gift table and layed a silver box on it which had saphires all around the edge and top, and inside are silver moon tea leaves which are gorwn in a hidden valley in India, and are picked in the moon light and the silver color stays on them forever, for that, they bring good fortune. <br><br>      Hypnos then walks over to Aphrodite,*** &quot;Have you seen Aglaia yet? She never has missed a wedding...&quot;  <p>~*~*~*~*~Thè göd öƒ §|èèp~*~*~*~*~        </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/20/01 11:45:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/ashraionline/cuts_images/thumbnails/large_images/Aish8.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Absence</span><hr size=1> ::walks into the throne room smiling softly and walking with little Adonis holding him by his hand. They both bowed to Hades, and Persephone takes her seat upon her throne by him and and sits with Adonis on her lap::<br><br>What a shame it is that we can't go to the wedding ::sighs and pats his hand:: But I think we should at least send a gift ::claps both her hands, a servants walks in with an opened wrapped box full of soft paper. Persephone takes a box and opens it up to show Hades. Inside are three necklaces, one made of rubies, another made of sapphire, and another made of diamonds. There are also three beautiful daggars inside with jewel studded handles and four jeweled rings. Two for the bride and two for the groom::<br><br>I think these will make for proper wedding gifts ::closes the box and has the servant seal it back up. The servant hands her a paper and a black feathered ink pin and a slate. She writes a letter explaining her and Hades absence, but wishes that they enjoy th